t=\tan(x/2)
\sin x=2t/(1+t^2)
\cos x=(1-t^2)/(1+t^2)
 \frac{\sin x-\cos x+1}{\sin x+\cos x-1}= \frac{2t-1+t^2+1+t^2}{2t+1-t^2-1-t^2}= \frac{2t(1+t)}{2t(1-t)}=\frac{1+t}{1-t} 
